## THE 4-TIER FLUX ISA — ALL PUBLISHED TO crates.io

```
SENSOR ──► mini ──► std ──► edge ──► thor ──► PLATO
(Cortex-M4)  (RPi)   (Xavier)   (Thor)
  21 ops     37 ops   35 ops    43 ops
   256B      heap     async     CUDA
  no_std     CLI      tokio     fleet
```

### Tier 1: flux-isa-mini v0.1.0 ✅
- `#![no_std]`, zero heap, 256-byte stack, 24-byte fixed instructions
- 21 opcodes (stripped to essentials: ARITHMETIC + CONSTRAINT + COMPARE + FLOW)
- Sonar bounds checking (const-evaluated — MCU doesn't compute Mackenzie, just validates)
- 2-byte wire format (0x464C magic), zero-copy decode
- 7/7 tests, targets thumbv6m/thumbv7em/thumbv7m
- STM32 sensor gateway example: read SPI → LOAD depth → VALIDATE bounds → ASSERT safe → forward
- `cargo install flux-isa-mini`

### Tier 2: flux-isa-std v0.1.0 ✅
- Full std Rust, heap allocation, serde JSON serialization, clap CLI
- 37 opcodes, file persistence, bytecode save/load
- Quality gate: rejects absolute claims, too-short answers, missing fields
- Mackenzie 1981 sound speed + Francois-Garrison 1982 absorption
- CLI: `flux run file.flux`, `flux validate`, `flux disassemble`, `flux compile --csp spec.json`
- 19/19 tests (14 integration + 5 unit)
- Cross-compile for ARM: `cargo build --target armv7-unknown-linux-gnueabihf`
- `cargo install flux-isa-std`

### Tier 3: flux-isa-edge v0.1.0 ✅
- Async tokio runtime, Axum HTTP + WebSocket server
- PLATO client with exponential backoff retry + offline mode + local cache + background sync
- Sensor pipeline: SensorSource trait → FLUX validate → forward, with backpressure via bounded tokio channels
- Sonar sensor: Mackenzie sound speed, Francois-Garrison absorption, auto-compile validation rules to FLUX at init
- HTTP endpoints: POST /execute, POST /validate, GET /status, GET /health, WebSocket /stream
- Config via FLUX_* env vars, graceful shutdown with state persistence
- 25/25 tests
- Deployment: Jetson Xavier NX, NanoPi, any ARM64 Linux with 2GB+ RAM
- `cargo install flux-isa-edge`

### Tier 4: flux-isa-thor v0.1.0 ✅ — THE FLAGSHIP
- 43 opcodes: 35 base + 8 Thor extensions:
  - PARALLEL_BRANCH (0x80): fan-out to N parallel execution paths
  - REDUCE (0x81): merge parallel results
  - GPU_COMPILE (0x82): compile bytecode to CUDA kernel
  - BATCH_SOLVE (0x83): solve N CSP instances on GPU
  - SONAR_BATCH (0x84): batch sonar physics on GPU
  - TILE_COMMIT (0x85): commit verified result to PLATO
  - PATHFIND (0x86): traverse PLATO knowledge graph
- CUDA FFI: BatchCspSolver, BatchSonarPhysics, auto-routes CPU↔GPU based on batch size
- 5-stage pipeline: INGEST → VALIDATE → COMPILE → EXECUTE → COMMIT, each stage a tokio task connected by bounded channels with backpressure
- PLATO integration: async client with connection pooling, LRU cache, Pathfinder BFS with confidence-weighted edges
- Fleet coordination: FleetCoordinator discovers nodes, assigns tasks, collects results. I2I protocol: TASK/STATUS/CHECKPOINT/BLOCKER/DELIVERABLE
- Axum server: 8 HTTP endpoints + WebSocket + Prometheus metrics
- 21/21 tests, cargo check clean
- 5,971 lines across 26 files
- Deployment: Jetson Thor, AGX Orin, data center GPU (A100/H100)
- `cargo install flux-isa-thor`

